# Cursor Rules for SPK Network 2.0

## Tech Stack
- Frontend: React 18, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS v4, Wouter, TanStack Query
- Backend: Express.js, PostgreSQL, Drizzle ORM
- Desktop: Electron, electron-builder, electron-updater
- Storage: IPFS (Kubo/Helia)
- Blockchain: Hive (@hiveio/dhive)

## Project Structure
- `/client`: React frontend
- `/server`: Express backend and services
- `/shared`: Shared types and database schema
- `/desktop-agent`: Electron application
- `/docs`: Project documentation

## Coding Guidelines
- Use functional components with React hooks
- Maintain strict TypeScript types
- Use Drizzle ORM for all database operations
- Follow the established service pattern in `server/services/`
- Ensure all new UI components are added to `client/src/components/ui` using shadcn/ui patterns

## Desktop Agent Specifics
- The desktop agent lives in `desktop-agent/`
- It uses `electron-builder` for packaging
- Auto-updates are handled via `electron-updater` and GitHub releases
